# Title: File Deleted Via Sysinternals SDelete
# Author: Roberto Rodriguez (Cyb3rWard0g), OTR (Open Threat Research)
# Date: 2020-05-02
# Level: medium
# Description: Detects the deletion of files by the Sysinternals SDelete utility. It looks for the common name pattern used to rename files.
# MITRE Tactic: Uncategorized
# Tags: attack.stealth, attack.t1070.004
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/file/file_delete/file_delete_win_sysinternals_sdelete_file_deletion.yml
# False Positives:
#   - Legitimate usage

TargetFilename IN ("*.AAA", "*.ZZZ") NOT TargetFilename="*\\Wireshark\\radius\\dictionary.alcatel-lucent.aaa"